{"name": "ecidacli", "metadata": {"name": "ecidacli", "version": "0.1.11", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://gitlab.com/ecida", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pyyaml", "importlib-metadata", "packaging", "kafka-python", "requests", "setuptools"], "summary": "The ECiDA-CLI for python to make things easier", "upload_time": 1733998039}, "documentation": ["# ECIDA\n\n```\nusage: ecidacli [-h] [-f MAIN_FILE] COMMAND ...\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n  -f MAIN_FILE, --main-file MAIN_FILE\n                        main file to process (example: main.py)\n\n  COMMAND\n    manifests           generate the kubernetes manifests\n    build               build the container and push it to container registry\n    version             print ecidacli version\n    create              create resources e.g. module and environment\n    init                Initialize the codebase\n```\n\n```\nusage: ecidacli manifests [-h] [-u USERNAME] [-s SECRET] [-d DIR]\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n  -u USERNAME, --username USERNAME\n                        username for container registry authentication\n  -s SECRET, --secret SECRET\n                        name of secret in the kubernetes-cluster\n  -d DIR, --dir DIR     directory to put yaml files [default: manifests]\n```\n\n```\nusage: ecidacli build [-h] [-u USERNAME]\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n  -u USERNAME, --username USERNAME\n                        username for container registry authentication\n```\n\n```\nusage: ecidacli create [-h] RESOURCE [name]\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help  show this help message and exit\n  [name]      Name of resource\n  RESOURCE\n    module    create a module\n    env       create a environment\n```\n\n```\nusage: ecidacli init [-h] NAME\n\npositional arguments:\n  NAME        Name of the first module\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help  show this help message and exit\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "ecida-templates.module", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "ecida-templates.module.create_module", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "EcidaModule", "xref": {"fqname": "Ecida.EcidaModule", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ecida-templates.module.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "M", "type": {"name": "EcidaModule", "xref": {"fqname": "Ecida.EcidaModule", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "ecida-templates.module.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ecida-templates.module.M", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ecida-templates", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "docker_interface", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "docker_interface.parse_image_name", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "image_name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Parses the image name to extract the registry (if any) and the repository name.\n\nArgs:\n    image_name (str): The image name in full format, for example, 'my-registry.com/this/image'.\n\nReturns:\n    tuple[str, str]: registry URL, repository name."]}, {"name": "docker_interface.get_credentials", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "-